---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="About">
  <div class="content">
    <h1>About DeFlock Safford</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 1.15rem;">
      A local research and advocacy project on mass surveillance in Graham County, Arizona.
    </p>

    <h2>What This Is</h2>
    <p>
      DeFlock Safford is a project of <strong>The Mnemosyne Research Institute</strong>, a research operation based in Safford. We document how surveillance technology actually works, where the data goes, and what residents can do about it, starting with our own county.
    </p>

    <h2>What We're Not</h2>
    <p>
      We're not anti-police. We're not claiming local officers are doing anything illegal. We're against a private, for-profit surveillance network with no warrant requirement, sold to our community, that we don't control and can't see into without filing for the records.
    </p>

    <h2>Our Standard</h2>
    <p>
      Every factual claim on this site links to a primary document or major news report. We distinguish what's documented from what's predicted. When a claim rests on an advocacy group's analysis rather than a government admission, we say so. We'd rather lose an argument than make a claim we can't back.
    </p>
    <p>
      Found an error? That genuinely matters to us, a wrong fact here would undercut the entire point. Tell us and we'll fix it or pull it.
    </p>

    <h2>Sources We Rely On</h2>
    <ul class="card-specifics" style="margin: 1rem 0;">
      <li>Primary documents: White House directives, ICE and Pentagon contract records, agency public-records responses</li>
      <li>Civil-liberties research: the Electronic Frontier Foundation, the ACLU, the Brennan Center</li>
      <li>Reporting: 404 Media, Fortune, TIME, the SF Standard, and Arizona outlets including AZPM, Tucson Spotlight, KGUN9, and KOLD</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Get Involved</h2>
    <p>
      The most useful thing you can do is <a href={`${base}records/`}>file a records request</a> and share what comes back. If you have documents, local knowledge, or a correction, reach the Institute through its main channels in Safford.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-banner">
      <h3>Start Here</h3>
      <p>One records request is how every successful campaign in Arizona began.</p>
      <a href={`${base}records/`} class="btn">Take Action</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
